# Git & CI Rules

## Commit Convention (Conventional Commits — enforced by commitlint)
Format: `type(scope): description`
Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`, `ci`
Scopes: `server`, `app`, `types`, `prisma`, `auth`, `bookings`, `availability`, `integrations`, `ui`

Examples:
  - `feat(bookings): add optimistic cancel with rollback`
  - `fix(availability): correct UTC offset for IST timezone`
  - `perf(slots): cache slot calculation result per schedule day`
  - `refactor(auth): extract token rotation to dedicated service`

## Branch Strategy
- `main`: production-ready only. Direct commits blocked.
- `dev`: integration branch. All PRs target dev.
- Feature branches: `feat/[scope]-[short-description]`
- Fix branches: `fix/[scope]-[short-description]`

## Pre-commit Hooks (Husky)
Run in order, block commit on any failure:
1. `lint-staged`: eslint --fix on staged .ts/.tsx files
2. `prettier --check` on staged files
3. `tsc --noEmit` (type check)
4. `vitest run --passWithNoTests` on files related to staged changes

## What Never Gets Committed
- `.env` files
- `node_modules`
- `dist/` or `.next/` build outputs
- Any file containing a real API key, secret, or token
- `console.log` statements (lint rule catches this)
- `TODO` comments (use GitHub issues instead)
